1
00:00:19,583 --> 00:00:22,000
Hi, everyone, Kaleido Star
is about to start,

2
00:00:22,083 --> 00:00:24,708
so make sure that your room is
brightly lit and that you're not

3
00:00:24,791 --> 00:00:26,875
sitting too close to the TV.

4
00:00:29,291 --> 00:00:30,500
Well, well, well.

5
00:00:30,583 --> 00:00:32,625
Have you ever made
something with your friends?

6
00:00:32,708 --> 00:00:34,166
Sure, it can be
hard work getting

7
00:00:34,250 --> 00:00:36,791
a bunch of people organized,
but when you all put your heads

8
00:00:36,875 --> 00:00:40,666
together you can come up with
some really amazing things.

9
00:00:40,750 --> 00:00:42,333
Just like our new show!

10
00:00:42,416 --> 00:00:44,500
I'm really proud
of how it turned out.

11
00:00:44,583 --> 00:00:47,916
So, you gonna come see it?
Are you? Are you? Are you?!

12
00:02:19,916 --> 00:02:22,583
It's amazing how quickly
time passes, isn't it?

13
00:02:22,666 --> 00:02:25,250
I know, I can't believe
it's already been two weeks

14
00:02:25,333 --> 00:02:26,708
since we moved in.

15
00:02:26,791 --> 00:02:29,583
Two whole weeks! And in all
that time, we haven't done

16
00:02:29,666 --> 00:02:32,750
any work on our company
or found day jobs.

17
00:02:32,833 --> 00:02:34,708
I know I told my Mom
and Dad not to worry,

18
00:02:34,791 --> 00:02:36,250
but now I don't know...

19
00:02:36,333 --> 00:02:39,750
Oh, I wish we had a bigger
place to practice in.

20
00:02:39,833 --> 00:02:41,166
I know.

21
00:02:41,250 --> 00:02:43,666
I just wish our dreams
would hurry up and come true.

22
00:02:43,750 --> 00:02:45,666
Don't worry. It'll happen, Sora.

23
00:02:45,750 --> 00:02:48,125
Right. Like mine just did.

24
00:02:48,208 --> 00:02:49,791
You all right, Sora?

25
00:02:49,875 --> 00:02:52,083
I was just thinking maybe we
could stage a pillow fight

26
00:02:52,166 --> 00:02:53,583
up on the tight rope.

27
00:02:53,666 --> 00:02:55,333
Uh but seriously Mia, Anna,

28
00:02:55,416 --> 00:02:58,333
please don't go flashing your
underwear around here, okay?

29
00:02:58,416 --> 00:03:01,083
We're all girls. Who cares?

30
00:03:01,166 --> 00:03:02,458
Yeah.

31
00:03:02,541 --> 00:03:04,791
No! Anna what if there's
a peeping Tom at the window?

32
00:03:04,875 --> 00:03:07,291
Or some lecherous spirit
in here watching us?

33
00:03:08,750 --> 00:03:10,500
Hey what did you just call me?

34
00:03:13,458 --> 00:03:16,250
'An Amazing Change
From Zero To Hero.'

35
00:03:22,375 --> 00:03:24,958
I almost forgot that Yuri's
first show at Kaleido Stage

36
00:03:25,041 --> 00:03:27,208
was going to open today.

37
00:03:29,083 --> 00:03:31,333
What do you think?
Should we go?

38
00:03:31,416 --> 00:03:34,500
I still can't believe
he sent us all an invitation.

39
00:03:34,583 --> 00:03:36,166
That was strange.

40
00:03:36,250 --> 00:03:39,000
It's like he's
daring us to come.

41
00:03:39,083 --> 00:03:40,958
So... should we?

42
00:03:42,083 --> 00:03:46,541
Welcome one and all to the
rebirth of Kaleido Stage.

43
00:03:47,750 --> 00:03:51,375
Today you will see things you
never dreamed were possible.

44
00:03:52,500 --> 00:03:56,791
Before your eyes, the phoenix
will rise from the ashes.

45
00:04:00,125 --> 00:04:02,291
He spent a lot on this show.

46
00:04:02,375 --> 00:04:05,166
I knew it. He just
invited us to gloat.

47
00:04:21,291 --> 00:04:24,125
I performed opposite
Layla on that stage.

48
00:04:24,208 --> 00:04:25,458
We made shows where

49
00:04:25,541 --> 00:04:28,291
everyone pushed themselves
to do their very best.

50
00:04:28,375 --> 00:04:31,583
But I guess that kind of Kaleido
Stage doesn't exist anymore...

51
00:04:52,333 --> 00:04:53,416
What's wrong, Sora?

52
00:04:54,250 --> 00:04:56,250
Are you looking
for someone down there?

53
00:04:56,333 --> 00:04:58,083
Oh. I was just wondering

54
00:04:58,166 --> 00:05:00,916
if Layla might've come here
to see the show today, too.

55
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:02,416
Yeah she might...

56
00:05:02,500 --> 00:05:05,125
Yuri probably sent her
an invitation, too.

57
00:05:05,208 --> 00:05:07,291
But I'll bet she was
too busy to come.

58
00:05:07,375 --> 00:05:09,750
I read in a magazine that
she's filming another movie.

59
00:05:09,833 --> 00:05:11,666
Guess she won't
do shows anymore...

60
00:05:11,750 --> 00:05:15,916
That can't be true! She's too
good to stop performing.

61
00:05:16,833 --> 00:05:18,291
Look, it's Yuri.

62
00:05:21,250 --> 00:05:23,166
Mister Yuri?
Could you sign this for me?

63
00:05:23,250 --> 00:05:24,041
Sure.

64
00:05:24,125 --> 00:05:25,750
Will you sign my program, too?

65
00:05:25,833 --> 00:05:27,750
I would be honored to.

66
00:05:31,541 --> 00:05:34,333
Uh do you guys know why
we're hiding down here?

67
00:05:34,416 --> 00:05:35,666
No...

68
00:05:43,250 --> 00:05:45,791
How about we rent the
Empire Stage for a few days?

69
00:05:45,875 --> 00:05:48,458
It's only three hundred
and fifty per show.

70
00:05:48,541 --> 00:05:51,458
Then we've only got
enough money for three shows.

71
00:05:51,541 --> 00:05:53,791
We've got to find
someplace cheaper.

72
00:05:53,875 --> 00:05:56,083
If we can't have a space for at
least ten days there's almost

73
00:05:56,166 --> 00:05:58,000
no point in doing a show there.

74
00:05:59,375 --> 00:06:00,041
You're right.

75
00:06:00,708 --> 00:06:01,333
Hey!

76
00:06:02,208 --> 00:06:03,916
Did you find someplace?

77
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:06,416
'Wanted: three acrobats to
perform at the grand opening

78
00:06:06,500 --> 00:06:07,958
of a seafood restaurant.

79
00:06:08,041 --> 00:06:11,458
Applicants must audition.'
They pay pretty well, too!

80
00:06:11,541 --> 00:06:14,208
Wow that's perfect!

81
00:06:14,291 --> 00:06:16,333
But what'll we do
for the audition?

82
00:06:16,416 --> 00:06:18,000
We'll think of something.

83
00:06:18,083 --> 00:06:21,625
Right. Getting this job's
gonna be a piece of cake.

84
00:06:21,708 --> 00:06:22,958
Yeah!

85
00:06:27,333 --> 00:06:28,333
This is it.

86
00:06:28,416 --> 00:06:29,875
Come on let's go get a job.

87
00:06:29,958 --> 00:06:31,166
Let's do it.

88
00:06:31,250 --> 00:06:35,541
You want to hire us! Yes!

89
00:06:35,625 --> 00:06:36,416
Yes!

90
00:06:36,500 --> 00:06:37,666
Yes!

91
00:06:37,750 --> 00:06:40,458
You got yourself a job!

92
00:06:40,541 --> 00:06:42,375
All right!

93
00:06:47,416 --> 00:06:49,666
Welcome to the Seaside.

94
00:06:49,750 --> 00:06:51,250
If we're just here
to hand out balloons

95
00:06:51,333 --> 00:06:54,208
and wear these costumes,
why'd he have us audition?

96
00:06:54,291 --> 00:06:56,500
At least you got
the crab costume.

97
00:06:56,583 --> 00:06:59,041
That's way funnier
than a shrimp any day.

98
00:06:59,125 --> 00:07:02,208
I know. But this is our job, so
we've gotta do our best, right?

99
00:07:02,291 --> 00:07:03,500
Right.

100
00:07:06,791 --> 00:07:08,708
Welcome to the
Seaside, everyone!

101
00:07:09,250 --> 00:07:09,875
Mia!

102
00:07:09,958 --> 00:07:11,083
Right.

103
00:07:14,416 --> 00:07:17,791
One for you, one for you,
one for you, one for you.

104
00:07:27,083 --> 00:07:29,458
I thought that I'd made
myself perfectly clear.

105
00:07:29,541 --> 00:07:31,625
You're to stand out there
and hand out balloons--

106
00:07:31,708 --> 00:07:34,625
if they like you too much
they won't want to eat seafood.

107
00:07:34,708 --> 00:07:35,666
Yes, sir...

108
00:07:35,750 --> 00:07:36,833
Come right in...

109
00:07:36,916 --> 00:07:38,416
...and have yourself...

110
00:07:38,500 --> 00:07:39,916
...some tasty...

111
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:41,666
...seafood!

112
00:07:41,750 --> 00:07:44,791
Look, from now on no talking.
Just hand out balloons to

113
00:07:44,875 --> 00:07:46,333
the people as they walk by.

114
00:07:46,416 --> 00:07:47,500
Yes, sir...

115
00:07:47,583 --> 00:07:49,750
Why'd he even bother
having us audition?

116
00:07:49,833 --> 00:07:51,916
Come on, we've gotta
keep smiling, Mia.

117
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:54,416
I'm taking a break,
hold down those balloons.

118
00:07:54,500 --> 00:07:55,416
What's she upset about?

119
00:07:55,500 --> 00:07:56,916
At least she got
to wear the crab.

120
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:58,583
It's humiliating
being a shrimp.

121
00:07:58,666 --> 00:08:00,375
Smile. Anna, come on...

122
00:08:00,458 --> 00:08:04,416
We've been smiling.
So much my face hurts...

123
00:08:13,333 --> 00:08:15,291
Come have some
delicious seafood!

124
00:08:15,375 --> 00:08:16,458
Yuri.

125
00:08:17,833 --> 00:08:18,833
No way!

126
00:08:24,041 --> 00:08:26,291
What what are you doing?

127
00:08:26,375 --> 00:08:28,375
Um well, we're...

128
00:08:40,875 --> 00:08:45,083
Hey, I'm sorry. You just look so
ridiculous in those costumes.

129
00:08:46,875 --> 00:08:48,125
Sora...

130
00:08:48,208 --> 00:08:50,291
Oh no, Mr. Killian!
You're not injured, are you?

131
00:08:50,375 --> 00:08:52,208
No, just caught off guard.

132
00:08:52,291 --> 00:08:53,916
Please accept my apologies.

133
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:56,541
I've reserved you
a special table inside.

134
00:08:56,625 --> 00:08:58,583
Please, follow me, Mr. Killian.

135
00:09:00,291 --> 00:09:01,416
You're fired.

136
00:09:01,500 --> 00:09:02,958
Last person I'd want to see

137
00:09:03,041 --> 00:09:06,083
when I'm dressed in
a crab costume is Yuri.

138
00:09:06,166 --> 00:09:07,500
You don't know

139
00:09:07,583 --> 00:09:09,791
what real humiliation is
until you dress like a shrimp.

140
00:09:12,083 --> 00:09:13,500
Yeah?

141
00:09:17,750 --> 00:09:19,375
Who-- Who's there?

142
00:09:24,166 --> 00:09:26,000
I'm back!

143
00:09:26,083 --> 00:09:27,458
Miss Sarah?!

144
00:09:27,541 --> 00:09:29,750
I asked your friend the
Policeman and he told me

145
00:09:29,833 --> 00:09:31,500
this is where you live now.

146
00:09:31,583 --> 00:09:33,333
So here I am.

147
00:09:34,416 --> 00:09:36,041
This is a lovely place!

148
00:09:36,125 --> 00:09:37,916
Did you finish your
training already?

149
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:41,291
Yep and I can sumo wrestle
with the best of them now.

150
00:09:42,166 --> 00:09:44,333
I thought the training
was for your singing.

151
00:09:44,416 --> 00:09:48,375
Heavens no! Where's the fun in
that? I think sumo's brilliant.

152
00:09:48,458 --> 00:09:50,750
You should all come with
me sometime for a seminar.

153
00:09:50,833 --> 00:09:54,333
But Sarah, shouldn't you be
seeing how the Boss is doing?

154
00:09:54,416 --> 00:09:57,708
What? Is something wrong
with Kalos? You must tell me.

155
00:09:57,791 --> 00:10:01,000
We just figured
you know well...

156
00:10:02,291 --> 00:10:04,500
You know, I haven't
heard anything from Kalos

157
00:10:04,583 --> 00:10:05,875
in more than a fortnight...

158
00:10:05,958 --> 00:10:07,458
What?!

159
00:10:07,541 --> 00:10:09,125
I think he's taking some time
alone to see what he wants to do

160
00:10:09,208 --> 00:10:10,708
with his life now.

161
00:10:10,791 --> 00:10:13,708
Why hasn't he talked to you?
Aren't you worried about that?

162
00:10:13,791 --> 00:10:14,375
Worried?

163
00:10:14,458 --> 00:10:15,708
That he's faithful.

164
00:10:17,166 --> 00:10:19,125
Oh, I don't need
to worry about that.

165
00:10:19,208 --> 00:10:22,000
After Sora's little trick at
Kaleido Stage, I feel pretty

166
00:10:22,083 --> 00:10:25,416
secure Kalos is still head
over heels in love with me.

167
00:10:25,500 --> 00:10:27,416
Right...

168
00:10:27,500 --> 00:10:30,250
And by the way, I found
a you job if you're interested.

169
00:10:31,500 --> 00:10:32,916
Good! Here it is.

170
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:36,416
It says they're looking for
performers at Marine Park?!

171
00:10:38,416 --> 00:10:41,000
I just happened upon this
flyer when I was in town.

172
00:10:41,083 --> 00:10:43,041
And I thought 'what have we
got to lose,' so I talked to

173
00:10:43,125 --> 00:10:46,208
the owner of the Marine Park
and set everything up.

174
00:10:46,291 --> 00:10:49,250
But we're only booked for one
day -- the day after tomorrow.

175
00:10:49,333 --> 00:10:50,625
The day after tomorrow?

176
00:10:50,708 --> 00:10:52,875
Sorry, girls, it was
the best I could do.

177
00:10:52,958 --> 00:10:55,416
They usually have a band
that plays on that stage,

178
00:10:55,500 --> 00:10:58,291
but that day they're going to
be off so we're going to be on.

179
00:10:59,333 --> 00:11:00,708
And one more thing:

180
00:11:00,791 --> 00:11:02,625
they're going to clear
the set tomorrow night,

181
00:11:02,708 --> 00:11:05,666
so we won't have a chance
to rehearse on the stage.

182
00:11:06,583 --> 00:11:08,000
Well?

183
00:11:08,083 --> 00:11:11,125
I can't wait to
perform again. Well?

184
00:11:11,208 --> 00:11:15,125
Yeah. We should do it, it's not
like we have any other offers.

185
00:11:15,208 --> 00:11:16,458
And if they like the company,

186
00:11:16,541 --> 00:11:19,291
maybe we can work for them
on a long-term basis.

187
00:11:19,375 --> 00:11:21,041
Thanks a lot, Sarah!

188
00:11:21,125 --> 00:11:23,291
I'm so glad this
worked out for everyone.

189
00:11:23,375 --> 00:11:25,125
You should take a shower
and a nap, Sarah.

190
00:11:25,208 --> 00:11:27,125
You must be exhausted.

191
00:11:27,208 --> 00:11:28,250
Good idea!

192
00:11:29,833 --> 00:11:30,875
Take your time.

193
00:11:30,958 --> 00:11:33,458
Now, what did I do
to deserve this?

194
00:11:34,958 --> 00:11:36,250
So, what should we do?

195
00:11:36,333 --> 00:11:37,791
Well, we don't have much time,

196
00:11:37,875 --> 00:11:40,125
so we probably shouldn't try
to do something with a story.

197
00:11:40,208 --> 00:11:41,500
It'd be too elaborate...

198
00:11:41,583 --> 00:11:43,875
Should we just work up
a couple routines, then?

199
00:11:43,958 --> 00:11:46,500
Hey. What do you think about
calling up everyone who was

200
00:11:46,583 --> 00:11:47,833
in 'Freedom' with us?

201
00:11:47,916 --> 00:11:49,166
That's a great idea.

202
00:11:49,250 --> 00:11:51,250
I'll send out an e-mail
to them right away.

203
00:11:52,541 --> 00:11:53,666
Layla too.

204
00:11:56,083 --> 00:11:58,583
I think we should ask Layla
if she wants to do it.

205
00:11:59,791 --> 00:12:02,833
I don't know that
she'd be interested...

206
00:12:02,916 --> 00:12:06,500
Yeah. But if Sora wants
to ask her, we'll ask her.

207
00:12:06,583 --> 00:12:09,375
All right. Let's go over
to her house and see.

208
00:12:25,041 --> 00:12:27,875
So we thought we'd get everybody
from 'Freedom' together

209
00:12:27,958 --> 00:12:30,458
and create our
own Kaleido Stage.

210
00:12:30,541 --> 00:12:33,875
And we'd like for you
to be a part of it, Layla.

211
00:12:33,958 --> 00:12:37,041
I've got a screen test today
and a costume fitting tomorrow.

212
00:12:37,125 --> 00:12:38,583
Sorry to disappoint you,

213
00:12:38,666 --> 00:12:41,875
but I'm too busy. I wouldn't
even have the time to rehearse.

214
00:12:41,958 --> 00:12:44,416
Besides, my Father's
handles my schedule now,

215
00:12:44,500 --> 00:12:46,541
and he feels I should do film.

216
00:12:46,625 --> 00:12:48,125
Are you happy with that?

217
00:12:48,208 --> 00:12:51,208
I mean, you seem to
really love performing.

218
00:12:51,291 --> 00:12:55,500
I won't disobey my Father; he
has my best interests at heart.

219
00:12:55,583 --> 00:12:56,875
But, Layla, that doesn't
mean you're never going

220
00:12:56,958 --> 00:12:58,666
to perform again, does it?

221
00:12:58,750 --> 00:13:01,625
I-- I was hoping I was hoping
we'd get to star opposite

222
00:13:01,708 --> 00:13:03,416
each other again someday.

223
00:13:05,583 --> 00:13:06,708
Sora?

224
00:13:06,791 --> 00:13:09,208
Yes?

225
00:13:09,291 --> 00:13:11,666
Have you gained weight
since I saw you last?

226
00:13:13,041 --> 00:13:15,666
You don't seem to understand
how hard it is to get yourself

227
00:13:15,750 --> 00:13:18,666
back in shape if you let
your training slide, Sora.

228
00:13:18,750 --> 00:13:21,458
I I guess you're right...

229
00:13:24,166 --> 00:13:26,125
It looks like Layla isn't
going to be joining us

230
00:13:26,208 --> 00:13:28,750
for our new show
at the marine park.

231
00:13:28,833 --> 00:13:31,750
I hope she can be happy with
following her Father's orders.

232
00:13:31,833 --> 00:13:33,041
Yeah.

233
00:13:36,333 --> 00:13:38,875
And you can get this
three-volume instruction video

234
00:13:38,958 --> 00:13:40,458
for just two hundred dollars!

235
00:13:40,541 --> 00:13:42,958
Wow!

236
00:13:43,041 --> 00:13:45,708
You're back already?
What did she say?

237
00:13:45,791 --> 00:13:48,250
She's too busy, just like
we thought she would be.

238
00:13:48,333 --> 00:13:49,750
Really?

239
00:13:49,833 --> 00:13:52,708
Well what a pity, but I'm sure
we'll make do without her.

240
00:13:54,375 --> 00:13:57,166
I got some
responses to my e-mail.

241
00:13:57,250 --> 00:13:58,583
Really?

242
00:13:58,666 --> 00:14:00,791
Yeah, from Elena, Jeanne,
Clair... Even from Emilio!

243
00:14:02,375 --> 00:14:04,000
And they're all coming!

244
00:14:04,083 --> 00:14:05,541
All right!

245
00:14:05,625 --> 00:14:07,625
We're gonna give that park the
greatest show they ever saw!

246
00:14:07,708 --> 00:14:11,208
I know. It's just too bad we'll
only be performing it for a day.

247
00:14:11,291 --> 00:14:13,125
What? What?

248
00:14:13,208 --> 00:14:15,375
And Rosetta...

249
00:14:17,166 --> 00:14:20,291
It's been a long time.
I've read your e-mail.

250
00:14:20,375 --> 00:14:23,000
I'll go there
immediately. Rosetta

251
00:14:23,083 --> 00:14:25,333
I sent her an invitation,

252
00:14:25,416 --> 00:14:27,791
but I never thought
she'd be able to come.

253
00:14:27,875 --> 00:14:29,250
Wow...

254
00:14:29,333 --> 00:14:31,708
Well, this is it,
this is where they live...

255
