I'd really appreciate it if you
shared that with the group.

269
00:14:58,416 --> 00:15:00,250
You know, I stopped by
to look at the stage

270
00:15:00,333 --> 00:15:01,916
on the way here and...

271
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:03,375
How's it look?

272
00:15:03,458 --> 00:15:05,833
The ceiling's a lot lower
than I thought it would be.

273
00:15:05,916 --> 00:15:08,833
I guess that rules out
maneuvers on the trampoline...

274
00:15:09,708 --> 00:15:11,875
And the stage is also
kind of a weird shape:

275
00:15:11,958 --> 00:15:15,041
it's really wide, but
it's not very deep at all.

276
00:15:15,125 --> 00:15:17,541
So I guess that means if
everyone does end up coming

277
00:15:17,625 --> 00:15:19,541
it'd be impossible for us
all to be on stage together

278
00:15:19,625 --> 00:15:20,958
at the same time.

279
00:15:21,041 --> 00:15:23,125
And Rosetta will be pretty
limited in what she can do

280
00:15:23,208 --> 00:15:25,000
with her diabolo.

281
00:15:25,083 --> 00:15:27,083
It's not the best
situation, is it?

282
00:15:28,416 --> 00:15:31,000
Why can't you just take
the roof off the place?

283
00:15:31,083 --> 00:15:32,291
Please, we're talking.

284
00:15:32,375 --> 00:15:33,916
It's not an ideal venue,

285
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:35,916
but I guess we'll have
to make the best of it.

286
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:38,750
I'm sure we can alter some of
our routines to work there.

287
00:15:42,208 --> 00:15:43,875
It may not be exactly
what we'd hoped for,

288
00:15:43,958 --> 00:15:47,291
but at least I'll be performing
again. I'm so excited!

289
00:15:47,375 --> 00:15:51,000
And we'll get to see Rosetta
soon, too. I can't wait!

290
00:15:54,208 --> 00:15:55,500
I'm free!

291
00:15:56,833 --> 00:15:58,500
Great! The jumps look great!

292
00:15:58,583 --> 00:16:00,750
Clair, Jeanne, could
you pick up your pace?

293
00:16:00,833 --> 00:16:01,958
Sure.

294
00:16:03,375 --> 00:16:05,708
It's good to be working again.
Don't you think so?

295
00:16:05,791 --> 00:16:07,500
Yeah. But still...

296
00:16:07,583 --> 00:16:10,166
I went to measure the
stage today and it's tiny.

297
00:16:10,250 --> 00:16:11,750
Jean told me it was
small yesterday,

298
00:16:11,833 --> 00:16:15,458
but I justI don't know how we're
gonna get half the cast on it.

299
00:16:34,583 --> 00:16:37,083
I wish we could do
something really big.

300
00:16:37,166 --> 00:16:40,458
I know, but if we did
we'd fall off the stage.

301
00:16:40,541 --> 00:16:41,625
I know.

302
00:16:48,458 --> 00:16:49,750
Rosetta!

303
00:16:54,541 --> 00:16:55,958
--Sora!
--It's been so long!

304
00:16:56,041 --> 00:16:57,416
I can't believe you're here!

305
00:16:57,500 --> 00:16:59,750
We're glad you could make it
on such short notice.

306
00:16:59,833 --> 00:17:01,666
We thought you'd be too busy.

307
00:17:01,750 --> 00:17:03,208
Not a chance.

308
00:17:03,291 --> 00:17:06,333
I'm never too busy for you,
Sora, 'cause I owe you too much.

309
00:17:06,416 --> 00:17:09,708
Besides, I'd be honored to
be part of your new company!

310
00:17:09,791 --> 00:17:12,083
Just to warn you the
stage is really small.

311
00:17:12,166 --> 00:17:13,708
So this is gonna be tough.

312
00:17:13,791 --> 00:17:16,958
That's okay. The Diabolo Battle
doesn't take much space.

313
00:17:18,458 --> 00:17:19,833
The Diabolo Battle?

314
00:17:19,916 --> 00:17:23,750
You mean, like the one
we did at Kaleido Stage?

315
00:17:23,833 --> 00:17:25,458
That's going to be impossible.

316
00:17:25,541 --> 00:17:27,500
Oh.

317
00:17:27,583 --> 00:17:28,541
But I thought...

318
00:17:29,875 --> 00:17:31,750
Rosetta?

319
00:17:31,833 --> 00:17:34,041
Well, guess I'll have to
come up with something else.

320
00:17:34,125 --> 00:17:35,750
Thanks so much!

321
00:17:35,833 --> 00:17:39,458
Okay, guys. Breaktime's over,
so let's get back to work.

322
00:17:39,541 --> 00:17:40,583
Yeah!

323
00:17:46,333 --> 00:17:47,250
What?!

324
00:17:47,333 --> 00:17:49,000
This must be some
kind of mistake.

325
00:17:49,083 --> 00:17:50,791
But didn't someone call you?

326
00:17:50,875 --> 00:17:53,250
Your show's been
canceled for today.

327
00:17:53,333 --> 00:17:55,250
Nobody told us about this.

328
00:17:55,333 --> 00:17:57,625
Can't you do something
to cancel the cancellation?

329
00:17:57,708 --> 00:17:59,500
But no one struck
the band's set,

330
00:17:59,583 --> 00:18:01,375
and it's too late
to strike it now.

331
00:18:01,458 --> 00:18:04,125
That means we have no place
for you to perform.

332
00:18:04,208 --> 00:18:05,208
I wonder...

333
00:18:05,291 --> 00:18:06,208
Huh?

334
00:18:06,291 --> 00:18:07,666
Did somebody
put you up to this?

335
00:18:07,750 --> 00:18:10,791
I'm not at liberty to --
I mean, no...

336
00:18:10,875 --> 00:18:12,875
This has Yuri
written all over it.

337
00:18:12,958 --> 00:18:14,458
Could be.

338
00:18:14,541 --> 00:18:17,375
It looks like he's beaten us,
so we might as well go home...

339
00:18:17,458 --> 00:18:20,416
But we can't give up
this easily can we?

340
00:18:20,500 --> 00:18:23,708
I mean, not when
everyone came all this way.

341
00:18:23,791 --> 00:18:25,916
Even Rosetta came to perform...

342
00:18:32,208 --> 00:18:34,750
Why can't you just take
the roof off the place?

343
00:18:35,791 --> 00:18:39,333
The roof... That's it!

344
00:18:40,625 --> 00:18:43,333
You're not serious!
You are, aren't you?

345
00:18:43,416 --> 00:18:44,750
The park's not going to pay us,

346
00:18:44,833 --> 00:18:47,125
so none of you have to do
this if you don't want to.

347
00:18:47,208 --> 00:18:48,583
Right.

348
00:18:48,666 --> 00:18:51,083
Don't be stupid. I came all
this way and I'm not gonna

349
00:18:51,166 --> 00:18:52,416
go home without performing.

350
00:18:52,500 --> 00:18:53,708
Rosetta...

351
00:18:53,791 --> 00:18:55,250
That goes for us, too.

352
00:18:55,333 --> 00:18:56,541
And me.

353
00:18:56,625 --> 00:18:57,583
Awesome!

354
00:18:57,666 --> 00:18:59,166
Thanks, guys!

355
00:19:01,458 --> 00:19:02,875
All right it's agreed.

356
00:19:02,958 --> 00:19:04,916
Everything in this
amusement park is fair game

357
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:06,416
to perform on today.

358
00:19:06,500 --> 00:19:08,916
And all the customers
are gonna be our audience.

359
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:11,375
And our costumes are
what we're wearing now.

360
00:19:11,458 --> 00:19:14,750
Then let's get this
show started. Ready?

361
00:19:14,833 --> 00:19:16,208
Yeah!

362
00:19:16,291 --> 00:19:19,541
Do you think that
this is gonna work?

363
00:19:19,625 --> 00:19:20,958
I guess we'll find out.

364
00:19:36,750 --> 00:19:41,500
The thinking man. The
running man. The falling man.

365
00:20:09,291 --> 00:20:10,541
Well, they're not on stage... 

366
00:20:12,166 --> 00:20:13,208
What's going on?

367
00:20:15,083 --> 00:20:16,041
Sarah?

368
00:20:16,125 --> 00:20:18,666
Oh, hello, Marion.

369
00:20:18,750 --> 00:20:21,875
Uh do you mind telling me
what's going on out here?

370
00:20:23,208 --> 00:20:26,166
They couldn't use the stage, so
they're performing out here.

371
00:20:26,250 --> 00:20:28,000
We had a change in plans...

372
00:20:28,083 --> 00:20:29,791
What's going on out here?!

373
00:20:29,875 --> 00:20:33,875
Hey you people get
off of my carousel!

374
00:20:33,958 --> 00:20:35,541
What are we gonna do,
what are we gonna do?!

375
00:20:35,625 --> 00:20:36,958
And... up!

376
00:20:39,375 --> 00:20:40,208
A rose?

377
00:20:47,750 --> 00:20:49,166
It's Dio!

378
00:20:49,250 --> 00:20:51,916
You mean the guy with the
whip from Theatrical Camp?

379
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:54,666
Yeah. I asked Mia to
send him an e-mail, too.

380
00:20:56,041 --> 00:20:57,833
Thank you so much
for showing up, Dio!

381
00:20:57,916 --> 00:21:00,458
I had some free time,
so I figured I'd drop by.

382
00:21:00,541 --> 00:21:02,583
You didn't tell me
he was so good-looking!

383
00:21:03,583 --> 00:21:05,291
It looks like it was a good
thing that we didn't have

384
00:21:05,375 --> 00:21:07,041
to use the stage then.

385
00:21:07,125 --> 00:21:08,333
I agree.

386
00:21:10,083 --> 00:21:14,083
I wonder if... If the person who
canceled the show today was...

387
00:21:21,708 --> 00:21:23,083
It was Kalos.

388
00:21:24,291 --> 00:21:26,541
If they'd performed on
that tiny little stage

389
00:21:26,625 --> 00:21:28,666
they never would've had
this kind of response.

390
00:21:30,500 --> 00:21:32,416
This is just like him.

391
00:21:32,500 --> 00:21:34,916
If only Layla could've
been here today...

392
00:21:36,625 --> 00:21:37,750
Hey, Sora?

393
00:21:37,833 --> 00:21:38,541
Hm?

394
00:21:38,625 --> 00:21:40,125
Who is that?

395
00:22:19,666 --> 00:22:21,625
That scared the pee out of me!

396
00:22:21,708 --> 00:22:23,041
I know...

397
00:22:27,041 --> 00:22:30,125
But who could
who could that be?

398
00:22:40,791 --> 00:22:43,458
That was our biggest crowd
draw since I opened this park!

399
00:22:43,541 --> 00:22:45,916
And so, thanks to the
appearance of the masked star,

400
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:48,125
the owner of Marine Park
owner offered us a contract!

401
00:22:48,208 --> 00:22:50,791
Not just a contract,
a long-term contract!

402
00:22:50,875 --> 00:22:53,166
I always thought Layla was
amazing, but this person is...

403
00:22:53,250 --> 00:22:54,500
Who is she, anyway?

404
00:22:54,583 --> 00:22:56,500
And how can we get her
to perform with us again?

